{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2992116b-ea17-47e3-a124-2832953db124","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **v5.0.0+** — this version adds Microsoft.Testing.Platform support.\n\n2. **Add the MSBuild property** to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Keep `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** — it's still needed but works alongside the new platform.\n\n4. **Add the platform package**:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n5. **Optional but recommended** — enable the new test runner in `Directory.Build.props` or your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nAfter these changes, `dotnet test` will use Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest. Your existing `[Test]`, `[TestCase]`, etc. attributes remain unchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"338cf2cf-4003-4f2a-a536-85b686b86692","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question — I don't need to explore a codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.\n\nKey steps to migrate NUnit from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. Update NUnit3TestAdapter to version 5.0+ (which supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n2. Replace `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` packages\n3. Add the appropriate MSBuild property or use the new runner\n\nLet me give a concise but accurate answer.","outputTokens":444},"id":"9b1cbbb3-8112-4a7c-87ba-d55f3db6d5eb","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:15.973Z","parentId":"8edb14d8-7043-4d33-a871-a7c73366a8f9"}
